        "content": "<p>I'm interested in stabilizing <code>-Z instrument-coverage</code> (as <code>-C instrument-coverage</code>). As far as I can tell from the tracking issue, I don't <em>think</em> there are any blockers; there are open issues but not showstoppers.</p>",
        "id": 258538837,
        "sender_full_name": "Josh Triplett",
        "timestamp": 1634820580
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Would a PR stabilizing the option, and a writeup for why the option seems ready to stabilize, be welcome?</p>",
        "id": 258538883,
        "sender_full_name": "Josh Triplett",
        "timestamp": 1634820598
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do <code>-C flag</code> additions need an MCP?</p>",
        "id": 258539713,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1634820899
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(in any case I think the steps you outline would indeed be welcome)</p>",
        "id": 258539819,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1634820944
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Okay, a <code>-C flag</code> is explicitly <a href=\"https://forge.rust-lang.org/compiler/mcp.html#public-facing-changes-require-rfcbot-fcp\">addressed in the MCP doc</a>. Its an example of something that requires an MCP, and furthermore, requires full team fcp (rather than a mere “second” from a team member).</p>",
        "id": 258540016,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1634821016
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But, oh, hmm. That same section lists a hypothetical process of first doing an MCP for <code>-Z flag</code>, and then later moving it to <code>-C flag</code> via a PR that needs approval via <code>rfcbot fcp</code></p>",
        "id": 258540245,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1634821088
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(was there an MCP for <code>-Z instrument-coverage</code> ?)</p>",
        "id": 258540288,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1634821101
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>At this point I <em>think</em> an MCP is not strictly needed, assuming the PR includes any missing info in terms of the motivation for the flag.</p>",
        "id": 258540418,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1634821147
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"116083\">pnkfelix</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/131828-t-compiler/topic/stabilizing.20instrument-coverage/near/258540288\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>(was there an MCP for <code>-Z instrument-coverage</code> ?)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Looks like it: <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/compiler-team/issues/278\">https://github.com/rust-lang/compiler-team/issues/278</a></p>",
        "id": 258540435,
        "sender_full_name": "Josh Triplett",
        "timestamp": 1634821154
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Okay great then, thanks Josh!</p>",
